parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window regulator can cause the window to fall into the door panel, making it difficult or impossible to close or open, which can lead to safety and security issues, such as increased risk of injury or theft.
symptoms: Windows falling into the door panel
inability to close or open windows
loud banging sounds
and windows becoming inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor can cause the motor to overheat, potentially leading to a fire, and can also cause discomfort and distraction while driving.
symptoms: Blower motor overheating
melting of wire casings
and failure of the blower motor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel overflow issue can cause fuel to spill onto the ground, leading to environmental hazards and potential fire risks.
symptoms: Fuel overflowing from the tank when filling up
and fuel spilling onto the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure (Fuel Leaks and Overflow)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks and overflow can cause a fire hazard, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel splashes out of the fuel neck without warning
fuel leaks out of the vehicle
fuel tank overflows when filling up
and the vehicle may experience a fuel leak during certain types of rear-end collisions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Repair Parts for Recall (Fuel System, Gasoline, Structure)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of repair parts for the recall can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, potentially causing accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The part needed to repair the vehicle is unavailable
the dealer is unable to provide a specific date for when the part will become available
and the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joint due to corrosion can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Abnormal sounds
loss of power
vehicle swaying
grinding noise
and sudden failure of the ball joint
which can cause the vehicle to dip or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the control arm due to corrosion can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Abnormal sounds
loss of power
vehicle swaying
grinding noise
and sudden failure of the control arm
which can cause the vehicle to dip or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of suspension components can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Abnormal sounds
loss of power
vehicle swaying
grinding noise
and sudden failure of suspension components
which can cause the vehicle to dip or lose control.
